🧠 The Clean Distinction

Infinite = no limit exists

Indefinite = a limit may exist… you just don’t know it

⸻

Read that again… slowly.

⸻

Infinite means:

there is no end.
not later…
not hidden…
not waiting.

⸻

Indefinite means:

the end is unclear.
not visible yet…
not defined…
but possibly there.

⸻

🧩 Feel the Difference

Infinite feels like:

it never stops.

⸻

Indefinite feels like:

I don’t know when it stops.

⸻

Subtle.

But powerful.

⸻

🔢 Examples

Numbers
	•	Counting forever → infinite
	•	“We’ll keep going for now” → indefinite

⸻

Time
	•	The concept of eternity → infinite
	•	A meeting with no end time → indefinite

⸻

Pain / Stress
	•	“This will never end” → feels infinite
	•	“I don’t know when this ends” → actually indefinite

⸻

That last one matters.

⸻

